        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 5:05PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 505 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northwest of Brevard, or near Graveyard Fields, moving
southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Brevard, Graveyard Fields, Looking Glass, Black Balsam Area, B.R.
Parkway-Black Balsam To Mount Pisgah, Balsam Grove, and Penrose.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
